HEADWORD: Propense
<hw>Pro*pense"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>propensus</ets>, p. p. See <er>Propend</er>.]</ety> <def>Leaning
toward, in a moral sense; inclined; disposed; prone; <as>as, women
<ex>propense</ex> to holiness</as>.</def> <au>Hooker.</au> --
<wordforms><wf>Pro*pense"ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Pro*pense"ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Propension</ent>⟦br⟧
